title: For Sale:  Persian Mauser Carbine M49
postcontent: Hello, please correct me if I'm mistaken in the description of this rifle!Unless I am mistaken, this is a M49 Persian Mauser carbine produced at the arms factory in Iran. There is not a lot of information you can find about these rifles, I will post one informal link below.These rifles are Iranian manufactured copies of Czech VZ24 rifles, which in turn are copies of German Karabiner 98ks. The Iranians purchased some Czech rifles under contract which should have Persian script on the side of the receiver, and on the graduations for the elevation adjustment, with a Persian crest top of the receiver. These rifles should should be marked BRNO. As I understand, the Iranians shortly after started to produce their own, which should have sight elevations in standard english numericals and the inscription on the side of the receiver should read "made by Army Arms factory."The serial number on this rifle matches the bolt. If there is a serial number on the underside of the barrel, I'm not sure if it matches. The stock appears to be an original Iranian Persian Mauser stock, however, the number on it does not match the bolt and receiver. I believe these stocks originally came with a brass slingplate, I could be mistaken. It is missing from the rifle. There is a little bit of damage on both sides of the forend of the stock around the barrel band. The front sight protective wings are also uniquely uneven. I've only shot this rifle once or twice, the bore seems to be in decent condition, it can hit torso plates at 200 yards repetitively. I have not tried to group this rifle on paper.Below is the link, (it is informal.) If any interested party has more information on these rifles, or if I made an error in the description, I would love to know.http://www.aliparsa.com/brno/brno.html
